# Project Architecture

## Folder Structure
- All folders live at the **project root** — there is no `src/` directory.
- Feature-based architecture: `features/<feature>/{components, hooks, types, constants.ts}`
- Routes live in `app/` and mirror the URL structure:
  - `app/(landing)/page.tsx` → `/` (landing page)
  - `app/sessions/page.tsx` → `/sessions` (session list)
  - `app/sessions/[sessionId]/page.tsx` → `/sessions/[sessionId]` (session editor)
- Shared components in `components/` (including `components/ui/` for shadcn primitives)
- Utilities in `lib/`
- Wireframes in `wireframes/*.pen` (design files for landing, sessions list, and editor shell)

## Dependencies
- Use **pnpm** for all package management (never npm or yarn)
- Next.js (App Router) with React 19 and TypeScript strict
- **Tailwind CSS v4** — no `tailwind.config.ts`; all tokens defined via `@theme inline` and CSS variables in `app/globals.css`
- shadcn/ui for UI components
- Monaco editor (`@monaco-editor/react` or similar) for the code surface
- Zustand only when cross-feature shared state is needed
- React Query only when async HTTP data fetching is needed (non-WebSocket)

## File Naming
- Components: PascalCase (e.g. UserCard.tsx)
- Hooks: camelCase with use prefix (e.g. useAuth.ts)
- Constants: camelCase file, UPPER_SNAKE_CASE values
- Types: PascalCase (e.g. UserProfile.ts)

## When generating code
- Read plan.md first for full context
- Follow the design tokens in `app/globals.css` (Tailwind v4 — no tailwind.config.ts)
- Reference wireframes/*.pen for visual layout reference
- Build one feature at a time in the order defined in plan.md
- Include all UI states: loading, error, empty, success

## Design Tokens (CodeSesh-aligned)
- Primary: `#ff3c00` (orange) — buttons, accents, active states, focus rings.
- Shell background: near-black (e.g. Tailwind `slate-950` / `#020617`) — editor workspace background.
- Shell surfaces: `#111827` — nav bars, panels, cards in dark mode.
- Landing background: `#F3F4F6` — landing page only (non-dark).
- Cards: `#0B1120` in shell, `#FFFFFF` on landing — card surfaces, popovers, elevated surfaces.
- Text (dark shell): `#F9FAFB` — headings and primary text.
- Text (light pages): `#0A0A0A` — headings and primary text.
- Muted: `#9CA3AF` (dark) / `#6B7280` (light) — secondary text, captions.
- Semantic success: `#16A34A` (green) — connection “connected” indicator, success.
- Semantic warning: `#FACC15` (yellow) — connection “reconnecting” indicator, soft warnings.
- Semantic error: `#DC2626` (red) — connection “disconnected” indicator, errors.
- Font: Figtree only, loaded via `next/font`.
- Buttons: fully rounded (9999px / 100% border-radius) — solid orange is the default primary style.
- Outline buttons: 1.5px `#ff3c00` border, transparent background, orange text; on hover, add a subtle orange-tinted background while keeping text/border orange.
- Inputs (single-line): fully rounded (9999px), matching button height and radius.
- Textareas, cards, popovers, dropdowns: `0.75rem` border-radius.
- Modals / dialogs: `1rem` border-radius (slightly larger to feel elevated).
- ALL sizes in rem. No px.
- Style: Replit-inspired dark editor shell with LeetCode-like clarity; content-first, minimal chrome, generous whitespace.
